        <div class="col-md-8">
            <h4 class="step-title">Step 2</h4>
            <h4>Create Rest By Example File</h4>
            <ul>
                <li>To generate rest2mobile code using the r2m tool, you need to provide a "REST by example" file that contains
                    a specification of actual REST request URLs and their expected JSON response.
                    Learn more about the syntax of Rest By Example files at the
                    <a href="https://github.com/magnetsystems/rest2mobile/wiki/Rest-By-Example-Specifications">rest2mobile Wiki</a>
		    and the <a href="https://github.com/magnetsystems/r2m-cli/blob/master/README.md">rest2mobile CLI GitHub</a> page.
                </li>
                <li>An example file is provided below. Copy and paste the following Rest By Example below into a file called <b>example.txt</b> in a directory of your choice.
<pre>+Name getTimeZone
+Request
https://maps.googleapis.com/maps/api/timezone/json?location=39.6034810,-119.6822510&amp;timestamp=1331161200&amp;sensor=true

+Response
+Body
{
   "dstOffset" : 0,
   "rawOffset" : -28800,
   "status" : "OK",
   "timeZoneId" : "America/Los_Angeles",
   "timeZoneName" : "Pacific Standard Time"
}</pre>
                </li>
            </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="col-md-2"></div>
    </div>
</div>

<div class="step-section clearfix">
